              <p class="card-text">
                Single-use plastic waste, such as straws, bottles, and packaging, is a major contributor to plastic pollution. These
                items are often used once and then discarded, and can take hundreds of years to degrade. They also pose a threat to
                marine life, as they can be mistaken for food and ingested, causing harm or death.
              </p>
